Definition.WordDefinition:
parse \parse\ (p[aum]rs), v. t. [imp. & p. p. {parsed} (p[aum]rst); p. pr. & vb. n. {parsing}.] [L. pars a part; pars orationis a part of speech. See {Part}, n.] (Gram.) To resolve into its elements, as a sentence, pointing out the several parts of speech, and their relation to each other by government or agreement; to analyze and describe grammatically. [1913 Webster]
Let him construe the letter into English, and parse it over perfectly. --Ascham. [1913 Webster]
